#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn29.21"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn29.21-50:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 29 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 29 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn29.21-50:0.2"
msgid "1. Nāgavagga "
msgstr "1. Dragons "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 21–50. Jalābujādidānūpakārasuttattiṃsaka → 4 (pts1)
msgctxt "sn29.21-50:0.3"
msgid "21–50. Jalābujādidānūpakārasuttattiṃsaka "
msgstr "21–50. Thirty Discourses On How Giving Helps to Become Womb-Born, Etc. "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn29.21-50:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn29.21-50:1.2"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Seated to one side, that mendicant said to the Buddha: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn29.21-50:1.3"
msgid "“ko nu kho, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo, yena midhekacco kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā jalābujānaṃ nāgānaṃ … pe … "
msgstr "“Sir, what is the cause, what is the reason why someone, when their body breaks up, after death, is reborn in the company of the womb-born dragons … "

msgctxt "sn29.21-50:1.4"
msgid "saṃsedajānaṃ nāgānaṃ … pe … "
msgstr "moisture-born dragons … "

msgctxt "sn29.21-50:1.5"
msgid "opapātikānaṃ nāgānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjatī”ti? "
msgstr "spontaneously-born dragons?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.246, sc2
msgctxt "sn29.21-50:2.1"
msgid "“Idha, bhikkhu, ekacco kāyena dvayakārī hoti, vācāya dvayakārī, manasā dvayakārī. "
msgstr "“Mendicant, it’s when someone does both kinds of deeds by body, speech, and mind. "

msgctxt "sn29.21-50:2.2"
msgid "Tassa sutaṃ hoti: "
msgstr "And they’ve heard: "

msgctxt "sn29.21-50:2.3"
msgid "‘opapātikā nāgā dīghāyukā vaṇṇavanto sukhabahulā’ti. "
msgstr "‘The spontaneously-born dragons are long-lived, beautiful, and very happy.’ "

msgctxt "sn29.21-50:2.4"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti: "
msgstr "They think: "

msgctxt "sn29.21-50:2.5"
msgid "‘aho vatāhaṃ kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā opapātikānaṃ nāgānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjeyyan’ti. "
msgstr "‘If only, when my body breaks up, after death, I would be reborn in the company of the spontaneously-born dragons!’ "

msgctxt "sn29.21-50:2.6"
msgid "So annaṃ deti … pe … "
msgstr "They give food … "

msgctxt "sn29.21-50:2.7"
msgid "pānaṃ deti … pe … "
msgstr "drink … "

msgctxt "sn29.21-50:2.8"
msgid "padīpeyyaṃ deti. "
msgstr "a lamp. "

msgctxt "sn29.21-50:2.9"
msgid "So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā opapātikānaṃ nāgānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati. "
msgstr "When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in the company of the spontaneously-born dragons. "

msgctxt "sn29.21-50:2.10"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhu, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo, yena midhekacco kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā opapātikānaṃ nāgānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjatī”ti. "
msgstr "This is the cause, this is the reason why someone, when their body breaks up, after death, is reborn in the company of the spontaneously-born dragons.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn29.21-50:3.1"
msgid "(Iminā peyyālena dasa dasa suttantā kātabbā. "
msgstr "(Each set of ten discourses of this series should be treated in the same way.) "

msgctxt "sn29.21-50:3.2"
msgid "Evaṃ catūsu yonīsu cattālīsaṃ veyyākaraṇā honti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn29.21-50:3.3"
msgid "Purimehi pana dasahi suttantehi saha honti paṇṇāsasuttantāti.) "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn29.21-50:3.4"
msgid "Nāgavaggo paṭhamo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn29.21-50:4.1"
msgid "Suddhikaṃ paṇītataraṃ, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn29.21-50:4.2"
msgid "caturo ca uposathā; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn29.21-50:4.3"
msgid "Tassa sutaṃ caturo ca, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn29.21-50:4.4"
msgid "dānūpakārā ca tālīsaṃ; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn29.21-50:4.5"
msgid "Paṇṇāsa piṇḍato suttā, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn29.21-50:4.6"
msgid "nāgamhi suppakāsitāti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "sn29.21-50:4.7"
msgid "Nāgasaṃyuttaṃ samattaṃ. "
msgstr "The Linked Discourses on dragons are complete."

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
